!iflang [english]

!begin_node Shell library
!html_name shel

This library contains functions to read information from the program
environment (such as the (!nolink [GEM]) desktop and similar applications), or to
write them; in addition they can take on the launch of other (!nolink [GEM])
programs. The following routines are available for this:

!begin_xlist [x shel_envrn] !compressed
!item [(!bullet) shel_envrn]
Obtains value of environment variable
!item [(!bullet) shel_find]
Searches for a file
!item [(!bullet) shel_get]
Reads from the environment buffer
!item [(!bullet) shel_help]
Outputs Help-texts
!item [(!bullet) shel_put]
Writes to the environment buffer
!item [(!bullet) shel_rdef]
Inquires the default program
!item [(!bullet) shel_read]
Reads command line parameters
!item [(!bullet) shel_wdef]
Sets the default program
!item [(!bullet) shel_write]
Launches application
!item [(!bullet) x_shel_get]
Read information from GENEVA.CNF
!item [(!bullet) x_shel_put]
Write information to GENEVA.CNF
!end_xlist

(!B)Note:(!b) Here special merit has been earned by shel_write, which as of
(!nolink [AES]) Version 4.0 (or MagiC 3) has made many other useful things
available, such as Shutdown of the system, resolution changes, (!nolink [AES])
broadcasting etc.

See also: About the AES ~ Style guidelines

!else

!begin_node Shellfunktionen
!html_name shel

Diese Bibliothek enth(!aumlaut)lt Funktionen um Informationen aus der
Programmumgebung zu lesen bzw. in diese zu schreiben; au(!sharps)erdem kann hier(!uumlaut)ber
der Start anderer GEM-Programme (!uumlaut)bernommen werden. Insgesamt stehen die
folgenden Routinen zur Verf(!uumlaut)gung:

!begin_xlist [x shel_envrn] !compressed
!item [(!bullet) shel_envrn]
Environment-Variable abfragen
!item [(!bullet) shel_find]
Datei suchen
!item [(!bullet) shel_get]
Aus dem Environment-Puffer lesen
!item [(!bullet) shel_help]
Ausgabe von Hilfetexten
!item [(!bullet) shel_put]
In den Environment-Puffer schreiben
!item [(!bullet) shel_rdef]
Abfragen des Default-Programms
!item [(!bullet) shel_read]
Kommandozeilenparameter lesen
!item [(!bullet) shel_wdef]
Setzen des Default-Programms
!item [(!bullet) shel_write]
Applikation starten
!item [(!bullet) x_shel_get]
Liest die Informationen aus der GENEVA.CNF
!item [(!bullet) x_shel_put]
Schreibt Informationen in die GENEVA.CNF
!end_xlist

(!B)Hinweis:(!b) Eine besondere Beachtung hat dabei shel_write verdient,
welches ab (!nolink [AES])-Version 4.0 (bzw. MagiC 3) viele weitere n(!uumlaut)tzliche
Dinge wie ein Herunterfahren des Systems (Shut-Down), Aufl(!oumlaut)sungswechsel,
(!nolink [AES])-Broadcasting usw. zur Verf(!uumlaut)gung stellt.

Querverweis: AES ~ Style-Guidelines

